# Domain Monitor Configuration
# 
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your settings.
# IMPORTANT: .env is ignored by git — your credentials are safe.
# Use: source .env (or equivalent) before running domain-monitor with --notify-email

# SMTP Configuration for Email Notifications
# ============================================

# SMTP server hostname
# Default: smtp.gmail.com (Gmail is recommended)
# Examples:
#   - Gmail SMTP: smtp.gmail.com
#   - iCloud Mail: smtp.mail.me.com
#   - Outlook: smtp-mail.outlook.com
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com

# SMTP server port
# Default: 465 (SSL/TLS)
# Use 587 for STARTTLS
# SMTP_PORT=465

# Your email address (sender)
# This is the address that SMTP will send from.
# For Gmail and iCloud, this must match your account email.
# REQUIRED if you use --notify-email flag
# Example: SMTP_USER=you@gmail.com
# SMTP_USER=

# Your email password or App Password
# IMPORTANT: Use an App Password, NOT your real password!
#
# Gmail (2FA enabled):
#   1. Go to myaccount.google.com/security
#   2. Under "How you sign in to Google", click 2-Step Verification
#   3. Scroll to the bottom → App passwords
#   4. Create a new app password (name it "domain-monitor")
#   5. Copy the 16-character password here (without spaces)
#
# iCloud Mail:
#   1. Sign in at appleid.apple.com
#   2. Go to Sign-In and Security
#   3. Create App-Specific Passwords
#   4. Copy the password here
#
# REQUIRED if you use --notify-email flag
# SMTP_PASSWORD=
